# 2.01..2.05: the build regenerates configure with autoconf2.69 (these
# pre-autoconf-2.50 trees ship no usable configure), which leaves the version
# substitution variables empty. support/mkversion.sh is then invoked with no
# -d version / -p patchlevel and bails ("mkversion.sh: usage: ..."), so
# version.h is never generated and the build dies at version.c. 2.05a ships a
# mkversion.sh compatible with the empty invocation and builds, so it stays.
2.05.0
2.04.0
2.03.0
2.02.0
2.01.0

# 2.0: modern gcc rejects the K&R-style prototype macro (stdc.h's __P) used in
# extern declarations such as print_rlimtype in eval.c.
2.0.0
